      <hr>
      <div class="mini-stats">
        <div><b>8 mo</b><span>Internship experience</span></div>
        <div><b>20.5%</b><span>Movement waste cut (ITC)</span></div>
        <div><b>2</b><span>Quick-commerce onboards</span></div>
        <div><b>8.58</b><span>MBA CGPA</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="why">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="tag leaf">WHY HIRE ME</span>
      <h2>Ground-level execution, brought back to brand thinking.</h2>
      <p>Most candidates pick one side of marketing. I've stood at the till, the shopfloor, and the strategy table — which means my plans survive contact with reality.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-card reveal"><span class="num">01</span>
        <h3>I've sold the product myself</h3>
        <p>Moved ~120 units of Fest Frut sugarcane juice face-to-face in 2 days — strategy I write is grounded in what actually gets a consumer to say yes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card reveal"><span class="num">02</span>
        <h3>GTM from zero to shelf</h3>
        <p>Owned pricing, incentives, logistics, and quick-commerce onboarding (Amazon, Blinkit) for a startup launch — not just the deck, the rollout.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card reveal"><span class="num">03</span>
        <h3>Big-company rigor, startup speed</h3>
        <p>ITC Food Division taught me Kaizen and SOP discipline; Reega Industries taught me how to move fast with none of that infrastructure.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card reveal"><span class="num">04</span>
        <h3>Insight-led, not opinion-led</h3>
        <p>Every positioning call — from clean-label messaging to elderly nutrition formulation — starts with consumer research, not a hunch.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="tag">KEY STRENGTHS</span>
      <h2>What I bring to a brand team.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="strength-grid">
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">◆</div><h4>Brand Strategy</h4><p>Positioning, narrative and consumer trust-building, tested on a real clean-label launch.</p></div>
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">▲</div><h4>Go-To-Market</h4><p>Pricing, incentive design, logistics and channel rollout planning, retail to quick-commerce.</p></div>
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">●</div><h4>Consumer Insights</h4><p>Market research that turns into product, label and messaging decisions — not just a report.</p></div>
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">■</div><h4>Pricing &amp; Channel Strategy</h4><p>Margin and incentive modelling for B2B and B2C channels, built for real P&amp;L conversations.</p></div>
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">◈</div><h4>Process &amp; Operations</h4><p>Kaizen, 5S and FIFO experience that means I respect supply chain reality when I design campaigns.</p></div>
      <div class="strength-card reveal"><div class="icon">★</div><h4>Cross-functional Execution</h4><p>Comfortable running content, sales and ops conversations in the same week.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="tag citrus">PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY</span>
    </div>
    <div class="summary-box reveal">
      Consumer-first marketer and MBA candidate (<span class="hl">2026</span>) with a strong foundation in brand strategy, GTM execution, digital marketing and integrated brand communications. I decode consumer behaviour through <span class="hl">market research and insight</span> to craft sharp positioning, campaign strategy, and brand narrative — equally comfortable with big-picture brand thinking and ground-level execution, from <span class="hl">360° campaign planning</span> to digital commerce and trade marketing.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="experience">
  <div class="wrap">
